
SIGN_CERT (1)                 ROA-PKI                               SIGN_CERT(1)


NAME

        sign_cert - signs a certificate or a CRL

SYNOPSIS   

        sign_cert tobesignedfile keyfile

DESCRIPTION
    
        The "tobesignedfile" is signed using the private key in the "keyfile",
        a ".p15" file.  The type of contents in the "tobesignedfile" are 
        designated by its suffix: ".cer indicates a certificate, and ".crl"
        indicates a CRL.

        Response messages:

          Usage: TBS filename, Key filename
          Finished OK
          Error in ...
          Couldn't open ...

       where the ellipsis is replaced with specific information.
                             

